<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chap_characteristic_equation">
  <title>The Characteristic Equation</title>
  <introduction>
    <objectives>
      <introduction>
        <p>
          By the end of this section, you should be able to give precise and thorough
          answers to the questions listed below. You may want to keep these questions
          in mind to focus your thoughts as you complete the section.
        </p>
      </introduction>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is the characteristic polynomial of a matrix?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is the characteristic equation of a matrix?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How and why is the characteristic equation of a matrix useful?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How many different eigenvalues can an <m>n \times n</m> matrix have?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How large can the dimension of the eigenspace corresponding to an eigenvalue be?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
